title: Central Park is finally enjoying snow after 701 days
text: Central Park is finally enjoying snow after 701 days - - Updated [0](https://www.kezi.com/video/central-park-is-finally-enjoying-snow-after-701-days/video_846e9c6e-6f01-5db5-aa71-c5250ae5d02a.html#comments) Weather Alert ...ICE STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM TUESDAY TO 10 PM PST TUESDAY... * WHAT...Significant icing expected. Total snow accumulations of up to one inch and ice accumulations of around two tenths of an inch. * WHERE...Central Coast Range of Western Oregon and South Willamette Valley. * WHEN...From 11 AM to 10 PM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Power outages and tree damage are likely due to the ice. Travel will be difficult. PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS... Travel is strongly discouraged. If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. Prepare for possible power outages.
